			<div class="col right_column wider ml-auto">

				







    <div class="fr-view">
        <h3>Senior Development Officer, Individual Giving</h3><p><strong><br class="Apple-interchange-newline"></strong><strong>DATE:&nbsp;</strong>July 2022<br><strong>DEPARTMENT:&nbsp;</strong>Fund Raising<br><strong>REPORTS TO:&nbsp;</strong>Vice President of Philanthropy<br><strong>STATUS:</strong> Permanent Full-Time<br><strong>SALARY</strong>: $80,000-85,000 Per Annum Plus Benefits<br><strong>LOCATION:</strong> Toronto<br><strong>TIME REQUIRED ON-SITE</strong>: 30% (approximate)</p><p><strong>We are:</strong></p><p>Second Harvest is Canada&rsquo;s largest food rescue organization and expert in perishable food recovery.  We rescue surplus, unsold food from across the supply chain and redistribute it to not-for-profits across the country to feed communities. Demonstrating our values of community, environment, integrity, and collaboration, we strive for No Waste. No Hunger.</p><p>In this newly created role, the <strong><em>Senior Development Officer, Individual Giving</em></strong> will support the development of the major gifts program at Second Harvest, and is responsible for cultivating, converting, and stewarding a pipeline of 100+ individual major gift prospects ($5,000+). We are looking for a seasoned, strategic individual who is passionate about building meaningful and impactful relationships to further our mission.</p><p><strong>You Will</strong></p><ul><li>Participate in strategic planning activities in collaboration with team members, to identify and implement fundraising goals/activities.&nbsp;</li><li>Work closely with the Vice President of Philanthropy and the Senior Manager, Philanthropy to develop and execute major giving fundraising campaigns and achieve annual fundraising targets.</li><li>Build and execute personalized moves management strategies for a pipeline of 100+ major gifts prospects, with a focus on one-to-one in-person engagements.&nbsp;</li><li>Working closely with our donor stewardship team, support the creation and execution of a major donor stewardship program designed to connect our donors with the impact of their support.</li><li>Develop and execute appropriate donor recognition tactics, ensuring the generosity of our donors is acknowledged in a meaningful way.&nbsp;</li><li>Proactively identify and research new major gifts prospects.</li><li>Collaborate with the Marketing &amp; Communications team to craft impactful, high-quality donor solicitation and cultivation materials.&nbsp;</li><li>Accurately track donor communications, touchpoints, and pipeline in the Raiser&rsquo;s Edge database.</li><li>Perform other related duties as required or assigned to support the overall goals of the organization.</li></ul><p><strong>You Are</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Fundraiser:</strong> You are very seasoned when it comes to soliciting donors and prospects for financial requests (with substantial proven success with individual giving and/or major gifts). You have significant and demonstrated success in securing $5,000+ gifts.</li><li><strong>Relationship Builder:</strong> You are able to leverage your passion for hunger relief and environmental protection to build meaningful connections with our supporters.</li><li><strong>Donor-Focused:</strong> You put the donor at the heart of your work and understand the power of effective stewardship and communication as a means to cultivate strong, long-term relationships.</li><li><strong>Collaborative:</strong> you have a positive, collaborative working style with the ability to manage competing interests with diplomacy.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Communicator:</strong> you have excellent writing, communication, and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Specialized fundraising training and/or accreditation would be considered an asset.</li><li>Proven abilities with donor management databases (specifically Raiser&rsquo;s Edge) would be considered an asset.</li><li>*Bilingualism (French and English) is strongly preferred.&nbsp;</li><li>Able to travel and have a Valid Class G driver&rsquo;s license (mileage compensated).&nbsp;</li><li>Flexibility to work some evenings and weekends as needed to accommodate donor schedules and/or attend Second Harvest events.</li></ul><p>Second Harvest requires that all employees be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 as defined by Health Canada. The Organization will comply with its obligations pursuant to the applicable human rights legislation and accommodate any prospective or current employee who is unable to be vaccinated for substantiated reasons, such as medical or religious reasons. Second Harvest&rsquo;s vaccination policy is available upon request.</p><p><strong>For more information about Second Harvest, visit:</strong><a href="http:// www.secondharvest.ca"><strong>&nbsp;www.secondharvest.ca</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>To Apply</strong></p><p><strong>Please submit your cover letter and resume on or before August 11, 2022, via email, with &ldquo;SENIOR DEVELOPMENT OFFICER, INDIVIDUAL GIVING&rdquo; in the subject line,</strong><strong>&nbsp;to <a data-fr-linked="true" href="mailto:humanresources@secondharvest.ca">humanresources@secondharvest.ca</a>. We would appreciate no phone calls or agencies.</strong></p><p>We encourage applications from individuals who self-identify as belonging to equity-seeking groups such as (but not limited to): racialized persons/persons of colour, women, Indigenous peoples, persons with disabilities, and LGBTQ2S+ persons.</p><p>We would like to thank all applicants for applying for this position, however you will only be contacted if your candidacy is being considered. Second Harvest is committed to an inclusive and accessible recruitment and selection process. Please let us know if you require any accommodations.</p>
    </div>


    



